# Star Citizen Linux Driver Guide - Use NVIDIA 570 Instead of 580

**Issue:** Star Citizen does not work with NVIDIA driver version 580. Use version 570 instead. **Steps:** 1. Enable SSH (`sshd`) in case of black screen. 2. Download NVIDIA Driver 570: [https://www.nvidia.com/de-de/drivers/details/254657/](https://www.nvidia.com/de-de/drivers/details/254657/). 3. Install manually: `chmod +x NVIDIA-Linux-*.run && sudo ./NVIDIA-Linux-*.run` (may fail to load `nvidia-drm` at the end). 4. Build and install DKMS module: `sudo dkms build nvidia -v 570.195.03 && sudo dkms install nvidia -v 570.195.03`. 5. Reboot: `sudo reboot`. 6. Verify installation: `nvidia-smi`. Star Citizen should now work correctly.
